President Obama welcomed President Giorgio Napolitano of Italy to the White House. They discussed various strategic issues, including Iran, Afghanistan, the Balkans, Middle East peace efforts, counterterrorism, and the global economy. President Obama expressed support for a strong, integrated Europe and efforts to strengthen the transatlantic relationship through the NATO Strategic Concept process. He also thanked President Napolitano for Italy's contributions to peace and stability worldwide, including deployments to Afghanistan, Lebanon, and the Balkans, as well as hosting American service members and their families. President Obama mentioned looking forward to meeting Prime Minister Berlusconi at the upcoming G8/G20 meetings and further cooperation between the US and Italy.